        <h2 align="left">Decompression Illness &ndash; A Simple Guide</h2>
		<img src="../sponsors/_images/DCI_Book.jpg" alt="Decompression Illness Book " width="85" 
	height="120" border="0" class="imgRight" />
        <p align="justify">This relatively recent book by  John Lippmann, DAN AP Executive Director is an invaluable resource for all  recreational scuba divers. It is a great book to have in-store for your team as  well as your diving students/clients. </p>
        <p align="justify">You can purchase a small quantity  of the books to make available in-store or for re-sale. </p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>We have a special offer for DAN  Supporters, where you can buy a quantity of</strong> <strong>10 books for only AUD$70. At only  AUD$7 per book it is exceptional value for what is a great tool for divers.</strong></p>
        <p align="justify">The book provides practical advice on the recognition, management  and prevention of DCI.&nbsp; The guide is  dotted with case studies designed to highlight to the reader the diversity of  diving experiences that have resulted in decompression illness; some even after  what would normally appear to be relatively conservative dive profiles.</p>
        <p><a href="../sponsors/_pdf/DCI_Book_Order_Form.pdf">CLICK HERE</a> to place an order.        </p>
        <h2>DAN AP Point-of-Sale Materials</h2>
        <p>Are you running low of DAN  promotional items? To re-stock your DAN point-of-sale materials all you need to  do is send an email to marketing@danasiapacific.org. Follow the link below and  let us know which item/s you would like and in what quantity.</p>
        <p><a href="../sponsors/_pdf/DANAP_Promo_Materials.pdf">CLICK HERE</a> to view DAN AP's current promotional materials  range.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
        <h2>Are Your DAN Posters / Brochures Visible In-Store? </h2>
        <p>To highlight your status as a DAN Supporter and advocate of  dive safety it is vital that you position your DAN materials in a highly  visible location within your dive centre. It is also important to ensure the  DAN brochures/flyers are placed on your countertop in the DAN promotional stand  you have been provided.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <h2><strong>Which DAN Branch Do My Divers Join?</strong></h2>
        <p align="justify">          As you know, the Divers Alert Network has numerous branches,  with each looking after a dedicated region. The DAN branch that a diver joins  is generally dependent on where they reside. The below information should  assist you in directing your divers to the relevant DAN branch to apply for  coverage. </p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Asia-Pacific</strong> www.danasiapacific.org <br />
          Residents of Australia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Fiji,  Indonesia, Malaysia, Vietnam, Singapore, Cambodia, Myanmar, Philippines,  Vanuatu, India, Solomon Islands, Brunei, Thailand, Hong Kong, Korea, China and  Taiwan.</p>
        <p><strong>DAN America:</strong> www.diversalertnetwork.org<br />
        Residents of The United States and Canada</p>
        <p><strong>DAN Brazil:</strong> www.danbrasil.org.br/<br />
        Residents of Brazil</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Europe:</strong> www.daneurope.org<br />
        Residents of Geographical Europe, European Territories, and  Protectorates, with regional IDAN responsibility for the countries of the  Mediterranean Basin, the countries on the shores of the Red Sea, the Middle  East including the Persian Gulf, the countries on the shores of the Indian  Ocean north of the Equator, as well as the related overseas territories,  districts, and protectorates.</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Southern Africa:</strong> www.dansa.org<br />
        Residents of South Africa, Swaziland, Lesotho, Namibia,  Botswana, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Angola, Zambia, Zaire, Malawi, Tanzania, Kenya,  Madagascar, Comoros, Seychelles, and Mauritius.</p>
        <p><strong>DAN Japan:</strong> www.danjapan.gr.jp <br />
        Residents of Japanese mainland and islands.</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN World: </strong>www.diversalertnetwork.org/world/default.aspx<br />
          Residents of the Caribbean, Polynesia, Micronesia and  Melanesia (except Fiji), Puerto Rico, Guam, Bahamas, British and US Virgin  Islands, Central and South America.</p>
        <p align="justify"><em>The branch of DAN a diver joins in dependent on the country  they reside. E.g. If your diver lives in Australia they need to apply for  coverage via DAN Asia-Pacific. </em></p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>IMPORTANT</strong><br />
        * It is vital to note that each DAN affiliate organisation  offers somewhat different coverage options. As such applicants should be  encouraged to review the coverage options carefully on the above websites.</p>
        <p align="justify">* It is essential that divers understand what their DAN  coverage includes and also their policy restrictions. If a diver is unsure  please encourage them to contact the relevant DAN office.&nbsp; </p>
        <h2><strong>Until Next Time ....</strong></h2>
        <p align="justify">We will continue sharing with you  important issues, such as the increased incidence of serious ear injuries, as  well as calls for help and case studies. We hope this information will further  encourage you to prepare yourself, your team and your diving clients to be  prepared in the event of a diving accident or illness. </p>
        <p align="justify">Being prepared takes several forms, such as having the  skills to assist in a diving emergency, having a sufficient supply of oxygen  on-hand to help the diver in trouble, and being a member of an organisation  that is dedicated to helping divers in trouble and improving the safety of  diving. </p>
        <p align="justify">If you have a question that you would like to be addressed  we encourage you to send us an email. We are happy to assist you and your team  as best we can. If you have any recommendations as how we can reach more divers  in your area or how we can better work together, let us know. </p>
        <p>Let&rsquo;s work together to improve dive safety.</p>
        <p><em>Until next time safe diving,</em></p>
        <p>John Lippmann, Mel Cefai and the DAN Asia-Pacific Team</p>
